    <div class="navigation"> <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/2008/">Home</a></div> </div>
                	<h2 class="page-title">Openmoko codesprint @ FSCONS 2008</h2>
                <!-- start main content -->
    <div class="entry"> 
   
  <p>The Openmoko code sprint will focus on the developement of "voj". A tool to record, store and share your travel-routes using an Openmoko device. To allow a wide range of applications Voj will, following the example of "locations", integrate with the OpenStreeMap infrastructure and use the freely licensed maps to graphically display the routes.</p>
<p>What we have:</p>
<p>Humanware<br />
- 2 Openmoko developers (both python and edje experienced)</p>
<p>Infrastructure<br />
- a room<br />
- a lot of chairs and tables<br />
- a local svn<br />
- a local network</p>
<p>Hardware<br />
- some FreeRunners to test the application/code</p>
<p>Software<br />
- access to the gps data transmitted to and from the FreeRunner</p>
<p>the Plan<br />
- an outline of the tool(s) to be build with lots of room for creativity and individual freedom<br />
- UI designs as guidelines for the designs (will be published here as soon as available)</p>
<p>What we need</p>
<p>Humanware</p>
<p>- brave, creative developers</p>
<p>Hardware</p>
<p>- one laptop per developer, preferably welded together by a yearlong fruitful relationship</p>
<p>Software</p>
<p>- enlightenment development environment up and running (on-site installation etc also possible, but self-experiment encouraged)</p>
<p>What we will develop:</p>
<p>Software<br />
- a mechanism to record routes<br />
- a mechanism to store routes<br />
- a mechanism to share the routes on OpenStreetMap</p>
<p><strong>for more information please contact: mirko AT openmoko.com</strong></p>
   
